de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.controller.datageneration.unit
Class Unit

java.lang.Object
  de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.controller.datageneration.unit.Unit

public class Unit
extends java.lang.Object

An unit is a standard of a weight or a measurement. There are different systems of measurement, like metric system, natural system, imperial system.

The weight and measurements object is based on Strategy pattern. It defines a family of algorithms, encapsulates each one, and makes them interchangeable. Strategy lets the algorithm vary independently from clients (Unit) that use it.

getWeightAndMeasurement

public WeightAndMeasurement getWeightAndMeasurement()
gets the weight or measurement unit. Use this method if isCustomized() evaluates to false. Otherwise you should use getWeightAndMeasurementCustom().

If you do not take this advise, then you've to cast it into the appropriate type by yourself.

Returns:
weight or measurement type

getWeightAndMeasurementCustom

public WeightAndMeasurementCustomized getWeightAndMeasurementCustom()
returns the weight or measurement unit. Before you try to get any unit, please check with isCustomized() the status. If it evaluates to true, then go on and use this method. But if it evaluates to false take the above method getWeightAndMeasurement() instead.

If you do not take this advise, then you've to cast it into the appropriate type by yourself.

Returns:
customized weight or measurement type

getName

public final java.lang.String getName()
gets the name of the current selected or used unit. This is only for displaying concerns.

Returns:
weight or measurement

isCustomized

public final boolean isCustomized()
sets the customized setting. If customized is enabled, the unit is handled in a slightly different way to handle customization.

If this method evaluates to true, then you should use the getWeightAndMeasurementCustom() method. If it evaluates to false, you can take the other method getWeightAndMeasurement() instead.

It's possible always to take the latter method, but when this method returns true, you've to do more work by yourself and to cast it into the approprivate type.

Returns:
is this unit customized? If the answer is yes, it's handled different, to reflect customization.
